The paper proposes a framework for query answering within an existential rule setting, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence and databases (cs.AI and cs.DB). The focus is on inconsistency-tolerant semantics, which is related to logic and reasoning (cs.LO). The paper also discusses inference strategies and modifiers, which are relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
